 Data Persistence & Profile Classification API

A backend API that aggregates data from multiple external services, processes it into a structured profile, stores it in a PostgreSQL database, and exposes endpoints for managing and retrieving profiles.



Base URL
https://datapersistent-api.vercel.app


Features
Multi-API integration (Genderize, Agify, Nationalize)
Data processing & classification
Persistent storage using PostgreSQL (via Prisma)
Idempotent profile creation (prevents duplicates)
Filtering support (gender, country, age group)
RESTful API design
Robust error handling & edge case coverage


Tech Stack
Node.js
Express.js
PostgreSQL (Neon)
Prisma ORM
Axios
UUID v7

External APIs Used
Genderize → Predicts gender
Agify → Predicts age
Nationalize → Predicts nationality


API Endpoints


1. Create Profile
POST /api/profiles

Creates a new profile or returns an existing one if the name already exists.

Request Body
{
  "name": "rachel"
}

Example Response (201 Created)
{
  "status": "success",
  "data": {
    "id": "019d9b9a-3fde-7029-bd80-a17a403f9bfc",
    "name": "rachel",
    "gender": "female",
    "gender_probability": 0.99,
    "sample_size": 1234,
    "age": 53,
    "age_group": "adult",
    "country_id": "CN",
    "country_probability": 0.85,
    "created_at": "2026-04-17T12:37:35.809Z"
  }
}

Idempotency (Duplicate Handling)

If the same name is submitted again:

{
  "status": "success",
  "message": "Profile already exists",
  "data": { ...existing profile }
}


2. Get All Profiles
GET /api/profiles
 Example Response
{
  "status": "success",
  "count": 3,
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "019d9b72-59c0-7629-b24b-bf91ebe04986",
      "name": "samuel",
      "gender": "male",
      "age": 59,
      "age_group": "adult",
      "country_id": "NG"
    },
    {
      "id": "019d9b94-ac0e-7469-9c84-c26e29bfe101",
      "name": "david",
      "gender": "male",
      "age": 64,
      "age_group": "senior",
      "country_id": "NG"
    },
    {
      "id": "019d9b9a-3fde-7029-bd80-a17a403f9bfc",
      "name": "rachel",
      "gender": "female",
      "age": 53,
      "age_group": "adult",
      "country_id": "CN"
    }
  ]
}


 Filtering

Supports case-insensitive query parameters:

gender
country_id
age_group
Example
GET /api/profiles?gender=female
Response
{
  "status": "success",
  "count": 1,
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "019d9b9a-3fde-7029-bd80-a17a403f9bfc",
      "name": "rachel",
      "gender": "female",
      "age": 53,
      "age_group": "adult",
      "country_id": "CN"
    }
  ]
}


Get Single Profile
GET /api/profiles/{id}
Example
GET /api/profiles/019d9b72-59c0-7629-b24b-bf91ebe04986
Response
{
  "status": "success",
  "data": {
    "id": "019d9b72-59c0-7629-b24b-bf91ebe04986",
    "name": "samuel",
    "gender": "male",
    "gender_probability": 0.99,
    "sample_size": 603089,
    "age": 59,
    "age_group": "adult",
    "country_id": "NG",
    "country_probability": 0.1258960220430007,
    "created_at": "2026-04-17T12:37:35.809Z"
  }
}


4. Delete Profile
DELETE /api/profiles/{id}
Example
DELETE /api/profiles/019d9b9a-3fde-7029-bd80-a17a403f9bfc
Response
204 No Content

Data Processing Logic
Age Group Classification
0–12 → child
13–19 → teenager
20–59 → adult
60+ → senior
Nationality Selection
Chooses the country with the highest probability from Nationalize API
Idempotency
Each name is unique in the database
Duplicate requests return the existing profile instead of creating a new one


Error Handling
All errors follow this format:

{
  "status": "error",
  "message": "..."
}


Error Types
400 → Missing or empty name
422 → Invalid input type
404 → Profile not found
502 → External API failure


Edge Case Handling
Genderize returns null or count = 0 → rejected
Agify returns null age → rejected
Nationalize returns no country data → rejected

CORS
Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *


Database Schema (Prisma)
model Profile {
  id                  String   @id
  name                String   @unique
  gender              String
  gender_probability  Float
  sample_size         Int
  age                 Int
  age_group           String
  country_id          String
  country_probability Float
  created_at          DateTime @default(now())
}

Running Locally
npm install
npx prisma migrate dev
node index.js
